Now Lambert is looking to the former Spain under-21 international to inject some guile into his midfield.

Canales joined Real Sociedad last summer after a three-year stay at Valencia following his departure from Real.

His time with Real was hampered by injury having been touted as one of Spain’s top prospects.

Canales played in Sociedad’s incredible 4-2 comeback win over his former side Real on Sunday evening.

 

